  "texts": [
    "As explained, all paths between 𝑋 and 𝑌 need to be considered, regardless of their direction.",
    "That is, 𝑋 → 𝑍 → 𝑌 is a type of path that we should consider, but also 𝑋 ← 𝑍 → 𝑌 and 𝑋 → 𝑍 ← 𝑌.",
    "Going back to the paths we considered earlier: if we are interested in the causal effect of Open data on Citations, there is a directed, causal path from Open data to Data reuse to Citations, but there is also a non-causal path between Open data and Citations that runs through Field.",
    "1 We call a path open when all the nodes, i.e.",
    "variables, on the path are open."
